F2020\u002F10\u002F2020-04-09T143107Z_406910156_RC221G9ZI234_RTRMADP_3_HEALTH-CORONAVIRUS-SOUTHASIA-2-e1602053463609.jpg?quality=80&strip=all\" alt=\"Work from home-India-Covid\" class=\"wp-image-1914203\"\u003E\u003Cfigcaption\u003EA tight schedule. \u003C\u002Ffigcaption\u003E","tagName":"figure","type":"CORE_IMAGE"},"YmxvY2s6Ym5Wbk9qRTVNVGN4TlRRPXwy":{"__typename":"Block","connections":[],"attributes":[{"__typename":"Attribute","name":"dateModified","value":"1602625323"}],"id":"YmxvY2s6Ym5Wbk9qRTVNVGN4TlRRPXwy","innerHtml":"When India entered a nationwide lockdown on March 25, a majority of companies made working from home mandatory. Almost seven months later, office reopenings are only partial, and guidelines remain strict. While working from home in India can have \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fqz.com\u002Findia\u002F1343149\u002Fbraving-mumbais-local-trains-during-monsoon-peak-hours\u002F?utm_source=email&utm_medium=coronavirus&utm_content=9953188\"\u003Ebig advantages\u003C\u002Fa\u003E, it’s also taking a toll on mental health. \u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003EA third of workers in India \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fqz.com\u002Findia\u002F1914182\u002Findians-struggling-with-work-from-home-says-microsoft-survey\u002F\"\u003Ehave been feeling more burnt out\u003C\u002Fa\u003E over the past six months, according to a recent survey from Microsoft. Some 40% say they are stressed by the lack of separation between work and personal life, while 35% said they feel disconnected from their colleagues. \u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003EThe ideal WFH setup—spatially, mentally, emotionally—is a topic of much discussion at Quartz, and if you’re looking for more resources check out our guides to \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fqz.com\u002Fguide\u002Fborderless-team\u002F?utm_source=email&utm_medium=coronavirus&utm_content=9953188\"\u003Eborderless teams\u003C\u002Fa\u003E, \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fqz.com\u002Fguide\u002Fhome-office\u002F?\"\u003Ethe home office\u003C\u002Fa\u003E, and \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fqz.com\u002Fwork\u002F1095920\u002Fhow-to-manage-employees-who-work-from-home-a-guide-from-quartz-at-work\"\u003Emanaging remote employees\u003C\u002Fa\u003E (also our series on \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fqz.com\u002Fse\u002Fcultivating-resilience\u002F\"\u003Ecultivating resilience\u003C\u002Fa\u003E). But one of the best tools we’ve found, other than a commitment to wearing pants during work hours, is talking to and commiserating with each other. So visit the Coronavirus: Need to Know newsletter and let us know \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fqz.com\u002Femail\u002Fcoronavirus\u002F1916933\u002F\"\u003Ehow you’re holding up\u003C\u002Fa\u003E.","tagName":"p","type":"CORE_PARAGRAPH"},"bnVnOjE5MTcxNTQ=":{"__typename":"Nug","id":"bnVnOjE5MTcxNTQ=","blocks":[{"__ref":"YmxvY2s6Ym5Wbk9qRTVNVGN4TlRRPXww"},{"__ref":"YmxvY2s6Ym5Wbk9qRTVNVGN4TlRRPXwy"}],"dateGmt":"2020-10-13T21:42:40","emailLists":{"__typename":"NugToEmailListConnection","edges":[{"__typename":"NugToEmailListConnectionEdge","node":{"__typename":"EmailList","emailListId":434610398,"listId":11090937,"name":"Need to Know: Coronavirus"}}]},"link":"https:\u002F\u002Fqz.com\u002Fbriefing\u002F1917154\u002Ffeel-the-burnout\u002F","modifiedGmt":"2020-10-13T21:42:40","nugId":1917154,"tags":{"__typename":"NugToTagConnection","nodes":[]},"topics":{"__typename":"NugToTopicConnection","nodes":[]},"slug":"feel-the-burnout","title":"Feel the burnout"},"YmxvY2s6WTI5c2JHVmpkR2x2YmpveE9URTNNVEV5fDQ0":{"__typename":"Block","connections":[{"__ref":"bnVnOjE5MTcxNTQ="}],"attributes":[{"__typename":"Attribute","name":"postId","value":"1917154"},{"__typename":"Attribute","name":"emailListId","value":"434610398"},{"__typename":"Attribute","name":"dateModified","value":"1602625396"}],"id":"YmxvY2s6WTI5c2JHVmpkR2x2YmpveE9URTNNVEV5fDQ0","innerHtml":"","tagName":null,"type":"QZ_POST_TOUT"},"YmxvY2s6WTI5c2JHVmpkR2x2YmpveE9URTNNVEV5fDQ2":{"__typename":"Block","connections":[],"attributes":[],"id":"YmxvY2s6WTI5c2JHVmpkR2x2YmpveE9URTNNVEV5fDQ2","innerHtml":"","tagName":"hr","type":"CORE_SEPARATOR"},"YmxvY2s6Ym5Wbk9qRTVNVGN4TnpVPXww":{"__typename":"Block","connections":[],"attributes":[],"id":"YmxvY2s6Ym5Wbk9qRTVNVGN4TnpVPXww","innerHtml":"If we ask you to think of climate change and urban design, you might conjure an image of solar panels and sea walls. But for many cities around the world, an even more important project will be \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fqz.com\u002F1895263\u002Fhow-cities-can-prepare-to-support-climate-migrants\u002F\"\u003Eimproving access to affordable housing\u003C\u002Fa\u003E. As people are forced to move away from communities that flooding, wildfires, and other climate impacts have made unlivable, they will need somewhere to go. A recent study projected that there may be \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fqz.com\u002Femails\u002Fquartz-obsession\u002F1898878\u002F\"\u003E13 million such climate migrants in the US alone\u003C\u002Fa\u003E by 2100.","tagName":"p","type":"CORE_PARAGRAPH"},"YmxvY2s6Ym5Wbk9qRTVNVGN4TnpVPXwy":{"__typename":"Block","connections":[],"attributes":[],"id":"YmxvY2s6Ym5Wbk9qRTVNVGN4TnpVPXwy","innerHtml":"The trouble is, the housing market in cities that could be “climate havens”—those that are relatively isolated from environmental impacts and have room to grow—is trending in the opposite direction. Of 10 US cities researchers identified as likely climate havens, all but one have seen the availability of affordable housing decrease in recent years, most faster than the national average:","tagName":"p","type":"CORE_PARAGRAPH"},"YmxvY2s6Ym5Wbk9qRTVNVGN4TnpVPXw0":{"__typename":"Block","connections":[],"attributes":[{"__typename":"Attribute","name":"url","value":"https:\u002F\u002Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net\u002F1MS1k\u002F3\u002F"},{"__typename":"Attribute","name":"type","value":"rich"},{"__typename":"Attribute","name":"providerNameSlug","value":"datawrapper"},{"__typename":"Attribute","name":"classNam